[Student "S"]
{South is to play 4\S. West leads the \DJ, covered by the \DQ and \DA. East returns a \D to the \DK.  

You still have two losers in the \H suit, so the question is which way you plan to finesse the \Cs. And of course the answer is that you don't plan to finesse them at all!

Pull trumps with the \SA, then \SK. Next ruff dummy's last \D.

Now exit with a \H. The defenders win this and take another \H trick, leaving this position.

They must now break the \C suit for you or give you a ruff-sluff. Of course you would ruff in dummy and discard a \C from the 3-card holding in your hand.

If East is the one who has to play a \C you just let it ride around to dummy's \C K J 10 3.  

If West is the one who has to play a \C you need to insert the \CT or \CJ from dummy.

In either case you will no longer have a \C loser.}
[Play "W"]DJ

